JOHANNESBURG - Family members and friends of the late struggle stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela are marking the anniversary of her passing with a wreath-laying ceremony at Fourways Memorial Park. Mam' Winnie, as she was affectionately known, died exactly four years ago at a Johannesburg hospital after a long illness. Gauteng Education MEC and the Deputy Chairperson of the ANC in the province, Panyaza Lesufi was among those who attended the ceremony. Lesufi said Madikizela-Mandela should be remembered as a selfless struggle icon who stood for social justice and equality for all.